		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, there are still some faint bars that are visible when certain lighter shades of color take up a large portion of screen: Zelda is a good example, in the area just south of the graveyard, right after you exit the Lost Woods.<br /><br />I don't have enough equipment with me to do a perfect A-B comparison, but just from playing one console for about 30 minutes and then switching to the other, to my eyes, the faint &quot;jail bars&quot; look the same on a toaster model. Without doing an A-B, though, it does look like the top-loader has slightly softer pixels, and the audio is a bit quieter, and possibly a slight bit more muffled.<br /><br />I am perfectly okay with this.<br /><br />It looks like I'm going to have to refurbish my toaster model if I want to enjoy Famicom expansion audio with an Everdrive, though.

		

